- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a graph-theoretical representation of proofs of multiplicative linear logic, which is a logical system. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper uses a locative approach related to game semantics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper discusses a denotational semantics and a notion of truth for a logical system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses graph-theoretical notions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses a categorical semantics for MLL, which is a logical system used in AI.
